1- Create a 10x10 Grid
2- Create the 5 players ship.
3- Assign Stretch Vertical or Horizontal
4- Assign a random position for the stretch of the ships but do not generate the ship
5- Validate that the random position the ship will be generate at will not go over the limit after applying the strech
6- Validate that once the strech is applied that there is not any enemy ship over that strech
7- If previous conditions are are met then generate the shit at that position with that stretch
8- If the condition are not met then repeat from step 4,
9- After Generating all the ships start the game


Other things to keep in mind:

1- Save unfishined game:
    So if the player quits their session I will save the game state to a binary file
    When the player decides to play again but the quit the session earlier they will be able to recover this session using B. or They can start a new session pressing A.

2- Showing Scores the lowest the score the better. I will show the 10 best scores


Functions to create:

1- A function to save the game state
2- A function to load the game.
3- A function to place the ships
4- A function to verify if it is a valid placement
5- A function to fire a missile
6- A function to check if it hit
7- A function to update the board
8- check if the ship is sunk, a ship will be sunk when all the coordinates it strectches from are hit.
9- A function to show the main menu
10- A function to start a new game
11- Running the main game through a loop


